---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
---

<Base
  title="About — DST"
  description="About the Dune Server Tool and its author."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="About"
    title="About DST"
    intro="A side project that grew up."
  />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-20 space-y-8 text-dune-muted leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      DST started as a handful of PowerShell helpers wrapping <code
        class="font-mono text-dune-accent-soft bg-dune-surface px-1 rounded"
        >kubectl</code
      > calls into a Dune: Awakening self-hosted VM. Over time it grew into a
      full local web portal — a single Windows app that owns the workflow of
      running, editing, backing up, and updating a Dune dedicated server
      without ever opening a raw SSH shell or hand-editing YAML.
    </p>

    <p>
      It's built and maintained by <strong class="text-dune-text">Coastal</strong
      > (Discord <span class="font-mono text-dune-text">@allcoast</span>),
      released under the Apache 2.0 license, and lives on GitHub at
      <a
        href="https://github.com/coastal-ms/DST-DuneServerTool"
        rel="noopener"
        class="text-dune-accent hover:text-dune-accent-soft"
        >coastal-ms/DST-DuneServerTool</a
      >. Bug reports, PRs, and forks are welcome — see <code
        class="font-mono text-dune-accent-soft bg-dune-surface px-1 rounded"
        >CONTRIBUTING.md</code
      > for the change-control workflow.
    </p>

    <p>
      For help, tips, and chat with other self-hosters, join the
      <a
        href="https://discord.gg/tj2x7cywSC"
        rel="noopener"
        class="text-dune-accent hover:text-dune-accent-soft"
        >DST community Discord</a
      >. New releases are announced there too.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dune-text pt-4">
      How it's put together
    </h2>
    <p>
      The native app shell is a Windows WebView2 host that loads a React +
      TypeScript + Tailwind frontend served by a local PowerShell HTTP +
      WebSocket server. The backend automates a Hyper-V VM over SSH, talks
      to a K3s cluster via <code
        class="font-mono text-dune-accent-soft bg-dune-surface px-1 rounded"
        >kubectl</code
      >, and reaches into the game's PostgreSQL database directly via <code
        class="font-mono text-dune-accent-soft bg-dune-surface px-1 rounded"
        >psql</code
      >. The installer is built with Inno Setup; CI runs on GitHub Actions; and
      the in-app updater pulls the next release straight from the Releases API.
    </p>

    <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 not-prose list-none p-0" aria-label="Technologies used">
      {[
        ".NET 10",
        "WebView2",
        "React",
        "TypeScript",
        "Tailwind CSS",
        "Vite",
        "PowerShell 7",
        "Hyper-V",
        "Kubernetes (K3s)",
        "PostgreSQL",
        "RabbitMQ",
        "SSH",
        "Inno Setup",
        "GitHub Actions",
      ].map((tech) => (
        <li class="font-mono text-xs text-dune-accent-soft bg-dune-surface border border-dune-border rounded-full px-3 py-1">
          {tech}
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>


    <p class="text-sm pt-8 border-t border-dune-border">
      Coastal is occasionally open to small consulting projects involving
      Windows tooling, server automation, or game-server operations — reach
      out on Discord (<span class="font-mono text-dune-text">@allcoast</span
      >) if that's relevant. No formal pitch, no rate card; just a quick
      chat.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
